{extends file="layout.tpl"}
{block name=body}
    <div class="row">
        <h3>How to use Pricer</h3>
        <ol>
            <li>
                <p>To use the program you need to register or log in</p>
                <div class="text-center">
                    <img src="/files/show/Pricer" class="img-responsive" alt="...">
                </div>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>By registering you will get access to the control panel</p>
                <div class="text-center">
                    <img src="/files/show/Pricer1" class="img-responsive" alt="...">
                </div>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>In the control panel you will see your templates. You can create new templates. Edit and delete old templates.</p>
                <div class="text-center">
                    <img src="/files/show/Pricer2" class="img-responsive" alt="...">
                </div>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>To create a new template you need to give it a name. Add price lists and their names.</p>
                <div class="text-center">
                    <img src="/files/show/Pricer3" class="img-responsive" alt="...">
                </div>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>After saving the template it will be possible to specify the fields you need for each price list</p>
                <div class="text-center">
                    <img src="/files/show/Pricer4" class="img-responsive" alt="...">
                </div>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>When editing the fields of the price list, you must carefully specify all parameters: the title, the order of the fields in the current and the resulting price. The fields are unique and the price is mandatory for each price. Other fields can be added at your discretion.</p>
                <div class="text-center">
                    <img src="/files/show/Pricer5" class="img-responsive" alt="...">
                </div>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>Fields are required to indicate their order in the incoming price</p>
                <div class="text-center">
                    <img src="/files/show/Pricer6" class="img-responsive" alt="...">
                </div>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>At each price, the order and the number of fields may be different</p>
                <div class="text-center">
                    <img src="/files/show/Pricer7" class="img-responsive" alt="...">
                </div>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>The main thing is to be attentive and to observe the necessary order. You need to do this only once. And you can use as many as you like.</p>
                <div class="text-center">
                    <img src="/files/show/Pricer13" class="img-responsive" alt="...">
                </div>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>After completing the field setup, you need to save the template.</p>
                <div class="text-center">
                    <img src="/files/show/Pricer8" class="img-responsive" alt="...">
                </div>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>A template will appear in the control panel. You can start generating your price list</p>
                <div class="text-center">
                    <img src="/files/show/Pricer9" class="img-responsive" alt="...">
                </div>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>Add files from your computer in the order you specified in the template</p>
                <div class="text-center">
                    <img src="/files/show/Pricer10" class="img-responsive" alt="...">
                </div>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>Click the button to generate the price</p>
                <div class="text-center">
                    <img src="/files/show/Pricer11" class="img-responsive" alt="...">
                </div>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>Get a ready file for work</p>
                <div class="text-center">
                    <img src="/files/show/Pricer14" class="img-responsive" alt="...">
                </div>
            </li>
        </ol>


    </div>

{/block}
